A man was killed while two others were seriously injured in a drive-by shooting outside a fast-food shop on Lenny Naidu Drive in Bayview during the early hours of Saturday, 1 May.  Amawele Emergency Services spokesperson, Sivan Subramodey said paramedics were called to the scene to find a vehicle riddled with bullets.  “Three men were shot multiple times. A man in his 30’s was found slumped in the back seat of the vehicle. He showed no signs of life. He was declared deceased at the scene. The body was handed to SAPS members. The other two men were transported privately to hospital for further treatment that they required,” he said. Bayview police are investigating a case of murder and attempted murder following the incident.